# Environment variables live per-app — see:
#
#   apps/storefront/.env.example
#   apps/marketplace/.env.example
#   apps/stripe/.env.example
#   apps/automated-tests/.env.example
#
# Copy each to `apps/<app>/.env` and adjust.
# Root-level .env is intentionally not used; Turborepo loads env from the
# package directory, and Next.js loads .env from each app folder via @next/env.
#
# The only script that still loads from a root-relative .env is the ledger
# migration helper, which reads `apps/marketplace/.env` (see migrate:ledger).
